          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, non-fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">The following substances were considered to represent AOX: trichloromethane (chloroform), chlorophenols, chlorobenzenes, dioxins and furans (EEA).
The ratio C fossil/C biogenic has been estimated to 50:50 using data concerning global material uses and mass flows (J.K. Steinberger et al., Ecological Economics, 2010, 69:1148–1158). Repartition of different fossil fuels was estimated using production volumes in ecoinvent v3.</comment>
